a 13-year-old boy with PH. <b>(a, b)</b> Axial thin-section CT images at the level of the aortic arch <b>(a)</b> and lower lobes <b>(b)</b> show diffuse bilateral centrilobular ground-glass opacities and interlobular septal thickening. <b>(c)</b> Axial CT image (mediastinal window) shows an enlarged main pulmonary artery.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2018170046&amp;id=fig12b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2018170046/asset/images/large/rg.2018170046.fig12c.jpeg" height="1243" width="1754" aria-labelledby="fig12c" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12c</span>. PVOD (group 1) in a 13-year-old boy with PH. <b>(a, b)</b> Axial thin-section CT images at the level of the aortic arch <b>(a)</b> and lower lobes <b>(b)</b> show diffuse bilateral centrilobular ground-glass opacities and interlobular septal thickening. <b>(c)</b> Axial CT image (mediastinal window) shows an enlarged main pulmonary artery.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2018170046&amp;id=fig12c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2018170046/asset/images/large/rg.2018170046.fig13a.jpeg" height="1236" width="1775" aria-labelledby="fig13a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span>. Diffuse solid nodules in a 43-year-old woman with a history of sarcoidosis (group 5). <b>(a, b)</b> Axial thin-section CT images at the infracarinal level <b>(a)</b> and lower lobes <b>(b)</b> show bilateral upper lobe areas of consolidation (arrows in <b>a</b>) and small nodules (arrowheads). There is also traction bronchiectasis, most evident in the 