onary artery <b>(b)</b> and lower lobes <b>(c)</b> show no pulmonary abnormalities.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2018170046&amp;id=fig17b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2018170046/asset/images/large/rg.2018170046.fig17c.jpeg" height="1285" width="1835" aria-labelledby="fig17c" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17c</span>. Idiopathic PAH (group 1) without mediastinal or pulmonary abnormality. <b>(a)</b> Axial CT image (mediastinal window) shows enlargement of the main pulmonary artery without any other associated findings. <b>(b, c)</b> Axial thin-section CT images (lung window) at the level of the main pulmonary artery <b>(b)</b> and lower lobes <b>(c)</b> show no pulmonary abnormalities.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2018170046&amp;id=fig17c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lang IM, Plank C, Sadushi-Kolici R, Jakowitsch J, Klepetko W, Maurer G. Imaging in pulmonary hypertension. <em>JACC Cardiovasc Imaging</em> 2010;3(12):1287–1295.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jcmg.2010.09.013">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21163459/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Imaging+in+pulmonary+hypertension&amp;author=IM+Lang&amp;author=C+Plank&amp;author=R+Sadu